	     Bloemfontein – A Free State police captain was left distraught after her son shot and killed himself with her gun, police said on Tuesday. Police spokesperson Ikobeng Hlubi said the boy's mother found his body at their home in Bloemanda in Bloemfontein on Monday evening. The boy was understood to have been alone at the time. "No suicide note was left and we are still unsure of the motive," Hlubi said. Hlubi said an inquest docket had been opened after the incident. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  